      "title": "libguides.fau.edu",
      "body": "<p><strong>Source queued:</strong> https://libguides.fau.edu/primary-sources-american-west/texas.</p><p><strong>Source type:</strong> Certification Training. <strong>Class-maker credibility tag:</strong> Primary.</p><p><strong>Source URL:</strong> <a href=\"https://libguides.fau.edu/primary-sources-american-west/texas\">https://libguides.fau.edu/primary-sources-american-west/texas</a></p><p>Texas - Primary Sources: American West - LibGuides at Florida Atlantic University Skip to Main Content Search Toggle navigation Ask a Librarian Hours Help Florida Atlantic University LibGuides Primary Sources: American West Texas Search this Guide Search Primary Sources: American West Welcome to the American West Primary Source Guide What is a Primary Source? General Sources Manifest Destiny Exploration Personal Narratives Arts &amp; Culture Literature Movies, TV and Radio Music Visual &amp; Fine Arts States Arizona California Colorado Idaho Kansas Montana New Mexico Oklahoma Oregon Texas Texas Online Sources: Texas Find Books Book Sources: Texas MEDIA : Texas Utah Washington Wyoming Cowboys &amp; Ranchers Homesteaders &amp; Pioneers Native Americans/American Indians This link opens in a new window Outlaws Gold Rush Logging &amp; Fur Railroads Newspapers This link opens in a new window Quick Links Need Help? Online Sources: Texas The Account of Felix Nunez Concerning the Fall of the Alamo This link opens in a new window Bexar Archives Online This link opens in a new window DPLA: Primary Source Set: Texas Revolution This link opens in a new window Harry Ransom Center Digital Collections This link opens in a new window Indian Relations in Texas This link opens in a new window Library of Congress: Primary Source Sets This link opens in a new window The Portal to Texas History This link opens in a new window Rangers and Outlaws This link opens in a new window Rare Book and Texana Collections This link opens in a new window Songs of Texas This link opens in a new window Texas 175: A Dozen Documents That Made A Difference This link opens in a new window Texas A &amp; M Digital Library This link opens in a new window Texas Constitutions 1824-1876 This link opens in a new window Texas Digital Newspaper Program This link opens in a new window Texas State Library &amp; Archives Online Collections This link opens in a new window Texas Tech University Libraries - Digital Collections This link opens in a new window Today in History: Remembering the Alamo This link opens in a new window University of Houston Digital Library This link opens in a new window University of Texas at San Antonio (UTSA) Digital Collections This link opens in a new window West Texas Collection This link opens in a new window William Barret Travis' Letter from the Alamo, 1836 This link opens in a new window “A Little Standing Army in Himself”: N. A. Jennings Tells of the Texas Rangers, 1875 This link opens in a new window Find Books Search the&amp;nbsp; FAU Library Catalog to see what materials are available for check out.&amp;nbsp;Search for books, government documents, DVDs, electronic books, streaming videos, and more. Book Sources: Texas Click the title for location and availability information. &amp;nbsp; Athanase de Mézières and the Louisiana-Texas frontier, 1768-1780 by Athanase de Mézières Call Number: Online - free - HathiTrust Documents pub. for the first time, from the original Spanish and French manuscripts, chiefly in the archives of Mexico and Spain ; tr. into English / ed. and annotated, by Herbert Eugene Bolton. Audubon's western journal, 1849-1850; being the MS. record of a trip from New York to Texas, and an overland journey through Mexico and Arizona to the gold-fields of California. by John Woodhouse Audubon Call Number: View Online HathiTrust Publication Date: 1969 British Diplomatic Correspondence concerning the Republic of Texas, 1838-1846 by Ephraim Douglass Adams Call Number: Online - free - HathiTrust \"The present publication consists mainly of letters and reports to the British government, hitherto unpublished, written by the two principal British officials stationed in Texas. They were Charles Elliot, chargé d'affaires, and William Kennedy, consul at Galveston.\" The Cowman's Southwest by Oliver Nelson Call Number: Online - free - HathiTrust being the reminiscences of Oliver Nelson, freighter, camp cook, cowboy, frontiersman in Kansas, Indian Territory, Texas, and Oklahoma, 1878-1893 / edited by Angie Debo. Diplomatic Correspondence of the Republic of Texas by George P. Garrison Call Number: Online - free - HathiTrust 1907-1908 Documents of Texas history Call Number: Online - free - HathiTrust Five years a cavalryman, or, sketches of regular army life on the Texas frontier, 1866-1871 by H. H. McConnell; William H. Leckie (Foreword by) Call Number: View Online ISBN: 9780806128177 Publication Date: 1996-03-15 Letters by lamplight a woman's view of everyday life in South Texas, 1873-1883 by Lois E. Myers Call Number: View Online ISBN: 9780918954695 Publication Date: 1998-06-30 Letters from an Early Settler of Texas by W.B. Dewees Call Number: Online - free - HathiTrust Letters relating to the History of Annexation by Anson Jones Call Number: Online - Free Book, 1852; digital images, (http://texashistory.unt.edu/ark:/67531/metapth6106/ : accessed March 10, 2014), University of North Texas Libraries, The Portal to Texas History, http://texashistory.unt.edu; crediting UNT Libraries, Denton, Texas. Memoranda and Official Correspondence relating to the Republic of Texas, its History and Annexation. by Anson Jones Call Number: Online - free - HathiTrust The Terán expedition into Texas and Louisiana by Florence Edith Barth Call Number: Online - free - HathiTrust Translation of the original documents with introduction and notes. Texas Chapter in American Freedom Call Number: Online - free - HathiTrust some of the historic documents of our Texas heritage. A Texas Ranger by J. Frank Dobie (Foreword by); Stephen L. Hardin (Introduction by) Call Number: View Online HathiTrust ISBN: 9780806129037 Publication Date: 1997-03-15 Texas Treasury papers; letters received in the Treasury Department of the Republic of Texas, 1836-1846. by Texas Call Number: Online - free - HathiTrust vols. 1, 3 and 4 The Texan-Santa Fé pioneers by Loomis, Noel M., 1905-1969. Call Number: Boca Raton General Collection ; F390 .L64 1958 Publication Date: 1958 MEDIA : Texas Texas Rangers: Manhunters of the Old West This link opens in a new window &amp;lt;&amp;lt; Previous: Oregon Next: Utah &amp;gt;&amp;gt; Last updated on May 4, 2026 10:17 AM Last Updated: May 4, 2026 10:17 AM URL: https://libguides.fau.edu/primary-sources-american-west Print Page Login to LibApps Report a problem Subjects: Arts &amp; Humanities Graduate Student Guides History Primary Source Guides Tags: African Newspapers American Indians American West Arizona History California History Colorado HIstory Cowboys Cowboys and Ranchers Explorations Fur Trade Gold Rush Homesteaders and Pioneers Idaho History Kansas History Logging Manifest Destiny Montana History New Mexico History Oklahoma History Oregon History Outlaws Primary Sources Railroads Texas History Utah History Washington State History Western States Wyoming History Florida Atlantic University Libraries 777 Glades Road Boca Raton, FL 33431 (561) 297-6911 Login to LibApps Report a problem.</p><div class=\"source-quality\"><p><strong>Credibility ranking:</strong> High. <strong>Reliability ranking:</strong> High.</p><p><strong>Information-literacy finding:</strong> Readable source text was available during generation. Use it for supported claims, and corroborate statistics, forecasts, or disputed points.</p></div>"
